Note:
HASHSET - Open-Addressing Hash Set Tier 0 Primitive

Like HashMap but stores only values, not key->value pairs.

Entry layout (16 bytes):
  offset 0:  state (8 bytes; 0 EMPTY, 1 OCCUPIED, 2 TOMBSTONE)
  offset 8:  value (8 bytes)

HashSet header (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  entries pointer
  offset 8:  capacity (power of two)
  offset 16: count
  offset 24: tombstones
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Let HASHSET_HEADER_SIZE be 32
Let HASHSET_ENTRY_SIZE be 16
Let HASHSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY be 16
Let HASHSET_STATE_EMPTY be 0
Let HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED be 1
Let HASHSET_STATE_TOMBSTONE be 2

@Reasoning
Mix integer to bucket index, same splitmix64 routine used in HashMap.
Different module, same algorithm, so an audit reviewing both can
cross-reference the identical mix logic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
splitmix64-style xor-multiply mix, then AND with (capacity - 1).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-cryptographic.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_index" takes value as Integer, capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    Let h be value
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 18397679294719823053
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 14181476777654086739
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Return h bitwise and mask
End Process

@Reasoning
Entry address.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
addr = entries + i * 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-validated index.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_entry_addr" takes entries as Integer, i as Integer returns Integer:
    Return entries plus (i multiplied by HASHSET_ENTRY_SIZE)
End Process

@Reasoning
Create empty HashSet with initial capacity 16.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate header and entries; zero-init entries.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_create" returns Integer:
    Let hs be proc allocate from Layout with HASHSET_HEADER_SIZE
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries_bytes be HASHSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY multiplied by HASHSET_ENTRY_SIZE
    Let entries be proc allocate from Layout with entries_bytes
    If entries is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with hs
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than entries_bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with entries, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 0, entries
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 8, HASHSET_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 24, 0
    Return hs
End Process

@Reasoning
Free HashSet.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free entries then header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_destroy" takes hs as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with entries
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with hs
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Probe for value. Returns slot index (occupied with match, or first
empty seen).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear probing with tombstone skip.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_probe" takes hs as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let idx be proc hashset_index with value, capacity
    Let first_tomb be 0 minus 1
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let addr be proc hashset_entry_addr with entries, idx
        Let state be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_EMPTY:
            If first_tomb is not equal to 0 minus 1:
                Return first_tomb
            End If
            Return idx
        End If
        If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED:
            Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 8
            If v is equal to value:
                Return idx
            End If
        End If
        If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_TOMBSTONE:
            If first_tomb is equal to 0 minus 1:
                Set first_tomb to idx
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to (idx plus 1) bitwise and mask
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Resize: double capacity and re-probe entries.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate new array, zero-init, re-probe each OCCUPIED entry. Free
old array.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n + capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_resize" takes hs as Integer returns Integer:
    Let old_entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    Let old_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 8
    Let new_capacity be old_capacity multiplied by 2
    Let new_bytes be new_capacity multiplied by HASHSET_ENTRY_SIZE
    Let new_entries be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
    If new_entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than new_bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with new_entries, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    Let new_mask be new_capacity minus 1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than old_capacity:
        Let addr be proc hashset_entry_addr with old_entries, i
        Let state be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED:
            Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 8
            Let new_idx be proc hashset_index with v, new_capacity
            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let na be proc hashset_entry_addr with new_entries, new_idx
                Let ns be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with na, 0
                If ns is equal to HASHSET_STATE_EMPTY:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with na, 0, HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with na, 8, v
                    Set new_idx to new_capacity
                End If
                If new_idx is greater than or equal to new_capacity:
                    Set new_idx to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Set new_idx to (new_idx plus 1) bitwise and new_mask
                End If
            End While
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with old_entries
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 0, new_entries
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 8, new_capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 24, 0
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Insert. Resizes on 75% load.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Resize if load >= 75%.
2) Probe; if OCCUPIED match, no-op return 1.
3) Else mark OCCUPIED + value, increment count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure during resize.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_add" takes hs as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 16
    Let tombs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 24
    Let cap be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 8
    Let occupancy be count plus tombs
    Let threshold be (cap multiplied by 75) divided by 100
    If occupancy is greater than or equal to threshold:
        Let r be proc hashset_resize with hs
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let idx be proc hashset_probe with hs, value
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    Let addr be proc hashset_entry_addr with entries, idx
    Let state be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED:
        Return 1
    End If
    If state is equal to HASHSET_STATE_TOMBSTONE:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 24, tombs minus 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 8, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 16, count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Probe; check if OCCUPIED with match.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_contains" takes hs as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx be proc hashset_probe with hs, value
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    Let addr be proc hashset_entry_addr with entries, idx
    Let state be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    If state is not equal to HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 8
    If v is equal to value:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Remove (mark TOMBSTONE).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Probe; if found, mark TOMBSTONE, decrement count, increment tombs.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_remove" takes hs as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx be proc hashset_probe with hs, value
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 0
    Let addr be proc hashset_entry_addr with entries, idx
    Let state be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    If state is not equal to HASHSET_STATE_OCCUPIED:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 8
    If v is not equal to value:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, HASHSET_STATE_TOMBSTONE
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 16, count minus 1
    Let tombs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hs, 24, tombs plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Size accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read count field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_size" takes hs as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Empty predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if count == 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hashset_is_empty" takes hs as Integer returns Integer:
    If hs is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let c be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hs, 16
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
